**Abstract:**
Research notes dated December 8, 1997 engaging James O'Donnell's Augustine: Confessions commentary. Develops critique of viewing Christianity as "a body of intellectual propositions" versus understanding religion as cult/liturgy. Includes extensive quotations from O'Donnell and Monasterio's reflections on the epistemological mistake of privileging written, objectifying language over narrative and practical knowledge.

**AI Recommendation:** Key text on cult versus doctrine; bridges Augustine scholarship to epistemology critique.

